HEADWORD: Elucidation
<hw>E*lu`ci*da"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧lucidation</ets>.]</ety> <def>A making clear; the act of
elucidating or that which elucidates, as an explanation, an exposition,
an illustration; <as>as, one example may serve for further
<ex>elucidation</ex> of the subject</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elucidative</ent>⟦br⟧
